Deployments.Status: As of May 2025, the Yara Birkeland, the world’s first fully electric and autonomous container ship, has been in commercial operation for three years since starting in spring 2022. Operated by Yara International, the vessel has completed over 250 voyages, transporting more than 35,000 containers between Yara’s production facility in Porsgrunn and the Port of Brevik in Norway. It has replaced approximately 35,000 diesel-powered truck journeys, reducing CO₂ emissions by 1,000 tonnes annually and decreasing noise and dust in populated areas.
